# YouTube Data API v3 key(s) -- comma-separated for a rotating pool.
# Each key gets its own 10,000-unit/day quota on the free tier. When the
# current key 403s with quotaExceeded the script rotates to the next.
# Single key: YOUTUBE_API_KEYS=AIza...
# Pool:       YOUTUBE_API_KEYS=AIza...one,AIza...two,AIza...three
# (The singular YOUTUBE_API_KEY is also accepted for back-compat.)
#
# Google Cloud Console -> APIs & Services -> Credentials -> Create API Key.
# Enable "YouTube Data API v3" on each key. For server-side use (this script),
# set the Application restriction to "None" (or IP-restrict to your dev box)
# and set the API restriction to "YouTube Data API v3" only.
# Do NOT use an HTTP-referrer restriction -- the Python client sends no
# Referer header and the request will be rejected.
YOUTUBE_API_KEYS=

# OAuth 2.0 Client ID (Desktop app type) for Drive / Sheets / Docs.
# Cloud Console -> APIs & Services -> Credentials -> Create Credentials ->
#   OAuth client ID -> Application type = "Desktop app".
# Enable "Google Drive API", "Google Sheets API", "Google Docs API" on
# the same project. Paste both values below.
#
# We use OAuth (not a service-account key) because most Google Workspace
# orgs enforce iam.disableServiceAccountKeyCreation, which blocks key
# creation. The OAuth flow is also a better fit for a manually-run script:
# output Sheet lives in *your* Drive and no long-lived JSON key sits on disk.
GOOGLE_OAUTH_CLIENT_ID=
GOOGLE_OAUTH_CLIENT_SECRET=

# Anthropic API key -- optional. With --with-pitches the script invokes the
# local `claude` CLI (Max Plan via keychain), NOT the Anthropic API, so this
# key is no longer required. Kept here only for any future scripts in this
# folder that might want the API path.
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=

# Optional: Google Drive folder ID to create "Tournamental GTM" inside.
# Leave blank to use Drive root.
# Get the ID from the folder URL: drive.google.com/drive/folders/<ID>
GOOGLE_DRIVE_PARENT_FOLDER_ID=

# Optional: path to a Playwright storage_state.json for logged-in YouTube
# scraping (unlocks "View email address" reveals behind YouTube's bot check).
# If unset, the tool looks for ./youtube_state.json by default. Produce one
# via auth_youtube.py from a browser cookies.txt export.
YOUTUBE_STORAGE_STATE=
